{"name":"Background: Brotherhood of Steel","permission":{"default":0,"Ks55FcjZarvIjLAC":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The Brotherhood of Steel is a neo-knightly order that rose from the ashes of the United States military in the years following the Great War of 2077. The organization's tenets include the eradication of mutants and the veneration of technology, specially pre-War technology. In recent years the Brotherhood has broken its trend of reluctance in sharing advanced technology with their fellow Wastelanders. The Brotherhood is mostly composed of the descendants of those military officers, soldiers, and scientists, but aside from some outsiders among their ranks, the Brotherhood is as close to pure-strain humanity (prime normals) that may be found outside of a Vault or the Enclave, with a few exceptions.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Skill Proficiencies: Athletics, Science</li>\n<li>Tool Proficiencies: Hacker Kit or Air Vehicles</li>\n<li>Equipment: A set of Scribe Robes or a set of Initiated Vestments, a laser pistol, 2 energy cells and 10 caps.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Feature: Tactical Hacking</strong>. You have been trained from an early age to be able to think quickly in stressful situations. You can use a Hacker Kit as a bonus action during combat.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/skills/weapon_21.jpg","_id":"TXTVUieEIoQAndw7"}
{"name":"Background: Knights of Nuka","permission":{"default":0,"Ks55FcjZarvIjLAC":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The KoN work out of a ruined bottling plant and a munitions factory next door. They use the machines and equipment to make some of the best guns available. They wear armor made from caps and can usually be found selling finely crafted weapons to fuel their expeditions to collect rare Sodas. They sell these guns out of an old Nuka Cola truck modified with sentry bot legs instead of wheels to help with rough terrain. In this “steed” they travel from settlement to settlement trading their wares.&nbsp; They have no interest in caps as currency and instead trade their weapons for unopened soda. They usually drink standard Nuka Cola, but other drinks are added to a giant stockpile in their base. Their ultimate goal is to find a legendary soda that is renowned as being transcendent in it’s flavor; Hank’s Root Beer.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Skill Proficiencies: Intimidation, Pre-War</li>\n<li>Tool Proficiencies: Land Vehicles</li>\n<li>Equipment: A set of Knight's Garb, 1 Martial Melee Weapon, 2 Nuka Colas, 5 caps.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Feature: Gun Connoisseur.</strong> The KoN are famous for making excellent guns. Gun crafters and merchants recognize you for a knowledgeable person and will give you access to better deals, higher quality guns and fine components.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/skills/mech_5.jpg","_id":"w8AsWlDQOPUUBlZM"}
{"name":"Background: Evolutionists","permission":{"default":0,"Ks55FcjZarvIjLAC":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The true children of the wasteland, the Evolutionists are a cabal of Ghouls, Super Mutants, and Monsters that believe their mutations are proof that they are the true inheritors of the earth. Their founder was a dedicated scientist that came to the realization that humans were no longer meant to rule the earth. He slowly began infecting his family and the settlements water supply with the FEV. With their support he began to spread his message to supermutants and ghouls that were shunned from human society due to their looks. Now they have become more aggressive with their tactics and small sects of extremists are terrorizing many settlements.&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Skill Proficiencies: Persuasion, Survival</li>\n<li>Languages: Mutant and Ghoul</li>\n<li>Equipment: A set of Evolutionist Garb, 1 Stimpak, 3 Prepared Meals and 10 caps.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Feature: Heirs of the Earth</strong>. The Evolutionists are popular amongst non-humans. As an Evolutionists you will always find shelter, food and care at exclusively non-human settlements. You also have advantage on Charisma checks to non-humans, made to turn them against humans.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/skills/affliction_02.jpg","_id":"Tr0jEIyO1rakDoMD"}
{"name":"Background: Chosen One","permission":{"default":0,"Ks55FcjZarvIjLAC":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You might seem like a normal person, but you are destined for so much more. Your destiny calls you to something greater, an epic quest that only you are aware of. It might've been told to you on a vision, or maybe it was written in the stars; however it happened, you found out about being special at some point in your life and now you have embarked on the path of adventure to conquer the goal you were born for.&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Skill Proficiencies: Choose two from Stealth, Persuasion, Deception, Survival, Investigation and Insight.</li>\n<li>Tool Proficiencies: One of your choice</li>\n<li>Equipment: Wastelander Outfit, a spear, 20 caps.</li>\n<li><strong>Feature: Epic Quest</strong>. You have been given a quest and you are the one destined to complete it. You have advantage on investigation and perception checks when they relate to your epic quest.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/skills/light_06.jpg","_id":"JeRz18mTeJSBJ5Fe"}
{"name":"Background: Courier","permission":{"default":0,"Ks55FcjZarvIjLAC":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Even in the new world order, people need things to be delivered through the dangerous Wastelands. When someone wants a package to arrive safely at a destination, they call you. You have traversed the arid territories between settlements and know how to keep a cargo safe. You don't question what you're delivering, and that's why people trust you.&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Skill Proficiencies: Athletics, Survival</li>\n<li>Languages: 1 extra</li>\n<li>Equipment: Courier Duster, a revolver, a lighter and 5 caps.</li>\n<li><strong>Feature: Courier Bag</strong>. You have a talent for stuffing your bag full and still finding just enough room. You can carry 20 lbs. more than you normally would.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/items/inventory/briefcase.jpg","_id":"RyOzjA6zhXubvMR9"}
{"name":"Background: Endless Walker","permission":{"default":0,"Ks55FcjZarvIjLAC":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are an exile from your people who were stripped of everything you had. You choose your story: where you used to dwell, whether it's a settlement, raiders, or other, and why you were kicked out of there. You have no place to call home and no one to call family.&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Skill Proficiencies: Any 2 skills</li>\n<li>Languages: One of your choice</li>\n<li>Tool Proficiencies: One of your choice</li>\n<li>Equipment: Nothing.</li>\n<li><strong>Feature: Sun Scorched</strong>. Your body has been tormented by the sun for so long, that your burns have deadened the nerves of your skin. You have resistance to fire damage.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/skills/blue_35.jpg","_id":"izXvkja4lwmXAbk0"}
{"name":"Background: Listeners","permission":{"default":0,"Ks55FcjZarvIjLAC":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are part of a group of people whose ears are naturally tuned to hear frequencies and volumes beyond the scope of normal human hearing. You can pick up the slightest electrical signal, which is powered by the fact that you live in and around the National Radio Astronomy Observatory in Pocahontas County. Once per day, you climb up the dish of the telescope to listen to the radio waves from the stars. At the end of the meditation, The Interpreter gives a sermon.&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Skill Proficiencies: Choose two from Religion, Percepción, Insight, Pre-War Knowledge, Deception, Persuasion</li>\n<li>Equipment: Listener's Vestments, a Simple Ranged Weapon, a radio and 10 caps.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Feature: Recall</strong>. Una vez al día ADV para tirada de INT, para recordar información que has oído.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/skills/blue_35.jpg","_id":"QmFSnDSkXHI8OZj1"}
